    <thetext>The ModuleEvaluationJob operation should be renamed to TopLevelModuleEvaluationJob to signal that it is only responsible for the loading of top level &quot;module scripts&quot; that are conceptually anonymous modules but really just acting as scripts with the Module non-terminal.

The role of TopLevelModuleEvaluationJob is only to parse and instantiate the top level module itself, but it assumes (with an &quot;Assert&quot;) that all transitive dependencies have already been instantiated.

See https://gist.github.com/dherman/cad85565e0eb16d0a22d for details.

Dave</thetext>
